        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p>Dr &amp; his Teachers for the Education &amp; Instruction<lb/> received, regretting
                the absence of his Father as he should<lb/> have wished to express<del>ed</del> to
                him his thanks &amp;<lb/> appreciation for having afforded him this<lb/>
                opportunity, in conclusion he bade a farewell<lb/> &amp; a friendly admonition to
                his schoolmates<lb/> After which the Rev Dr. presented every Scholar with<lb/> a
                premium according to their merits, <sic>adressing</sic><lb/> to each one a few words
                of praise, encouragement<lb/> &amp; admonition in a manner which showed that<lb/> in
                this institution the teachers make it<lb/> their duty to study the talents &amp;
                dispositions<lb/> of their pupils, by which alone instruction<lb/> can be
                successfully imparted F in<lb/> thanking his audience for their kind attention<lb/>
                <del>the Rev Dr.</del> remarked that after <date>Passover</date><lb/> he would get
                in addition to his present<lb/> teacher one for to teach the <sic>spanish</sic>
                language<lb/> &amp; will also introduce gymnastic Exercises,<lb/> as his new
                Building affording ample<lb/> room &amp; all convenience is under roof<lb/> &amp;
                nearly finished. We congratulate<lb/> our friend <persName>Dr L</persName> to his
                Success as<lb/> Pioneer in establishing a Hebrew Bdg School</p>
            <p>F In conclusion <persName>Dr. L.</persName>
                <sic>offerd</sic> his thanks to the Almighty for<lb/> his blessings &amp; in
                preserving all the pupils under his care<lb/> in good health—then presented
                    <persName>Eli Arnold</persName> with the 1st<lb/> gold <sic>metal</sic> awarded
                in his school.</p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>The semiannual examination of the <persName>Rev Dr. Lilienthal</persName><lb/>
                Boarding School took place on <date>Sunday last the 14<hi rend="sup">th</hi></date>
                inst at<lb/> his Residence in <placeName>NY</placeName> &amp; we learned with much
                pleasure<lb/> that such passed off to the great satisfaction<lb/> of the parents of
                the children &amp; all present.<lb/> The Scholars had a healthy &amp; cheerful
                appearance.<lb/> The <del>examination was</del> exercises were commenced with
                the<lb/> overture of <persName>Fra Diavolo</persName> on the violin by one<lb/> of
                the Scholars, &amp; after a Prologue by another<lb/>
                <persName>Dr. L</persName> begun the examinations <add>?</add> in Religion<lb/>
                &amp; Hebrew, then in Arithmetic, mechanical<lb/> Problems, Book keeping, Geography,
                History,<lb/> in the <sic>french</sic>, <sic>german</sic> &amp; <sic>english</sic>
                languages<lb/> with Exercises on the Piano &amp; Violin at<lb/> different intervals,
                while specimens of<lb/> Drawings &amp; Penmanship of all the pupils<lb/> were
                exhibited in an ante Room.<lb/> It would be consuming too much of this<lb/> space
                were we to name every one of the<lb/> Scholars, who <del>distinguished himself
                    or</del> deserved special notice; suffice<lb/> it to say that they must have
                used<lb/> their best exertions to excel &amp; that they<lb/> reflected much credit
                in themselves &amp; their<lb/> teachers. After the Examination was<lb/> concluded
                    <persName>Master Eli Arnold</persName> of their city<lb/> delivered his
                valedictory <sic>Adress</sic> in a very<lb/> happy manner, <del>compliments</del>
                thanking the Rev</p>
